      <elementaryExchange id="19d75a52-496d-5dc9-8c76-df4b5128c452" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" casNumber="007782-50-5" amount="6.181319494085765E-07" elementaryExchangeId="39d1390a-ded6-41cb-a536-d47510bf2fbc" formula="Cl2">
        <name xml:lang="en">Chlorine</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Estimation based on fuel input data and emission factors from corresponding ecoinvent fuel combustion datasets (see "Extrapolations" comment). The internal fuels mainly consist of the black liquor and bark from the wood input for pulp production. Internal fuels are represented by the calculated emissions but do not have the corresponding fuel input from technosphere, because they are supplied from within the system boundaries. The amounts of internal fuels used in the process are: Black liquor (8.203 GJ/t), Bark (1.372 GJ/t), biogas and biosludge (0.087 GJ/t), Refuse derived fuel (RDF) (0.024 GJ/t), and other internal fuels (0.114 GJ/t). No proxy was available for the combustion of black liquor, Refuse derived fuel, and other internal fuels. Emissions from these internal energy generation processes are therefore only reflected in the key emission factors provided by the industry, other emissions constitute a data gap.</comment>
        <uncertainty>
          <lognormal meanValue="6.181319494085765E-07" mu="-14.296563891908951" variance="0.04" varianceWithPedigreeUncertainty="0.05280000000000001"/>
          <pedigreeMatrix reliability="3" completeness="3" temporalCorrelation="2" geographicalCorrelation="5" furtherTechnologyCorrelation="3"/>
        </uncertainty>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">molecular chlorine</synonym>
